headline: Goldman Sachs (GS): Assessing Valuation After a 61% One-Year Share Price Surge
summary: Goldman Sachs Group (GS) keeps grinding higher, with the stock up roughly 7% over the past month and about 61% over the past year, as investors lean into its steady earnings recovery. See our latest analysis for Goldman Sachs Group. That strength reflects more than just a good month, with a 30 day share price return of about 7% building on a powerful 12 month total shareholder return of roughly 61% as markets re rate GS earnings power. headline: Goldman Says Venezuela Oil Output May Rise in the Long Term
summary: At the weekend, the US stunned the world by attacking the South American nation, seizing Nicolás Maduro, and saying that it was going to “run” the country.  While Venezuela was once an oil-producing powerhouse, output has declined precipitously over the past two decades.  Any recovery “would likely be gradual and partial as the infrastructure is degraded and would require strong incentives for substantial upstream investment,” analysts including Daan Struyven said in a note on Sunday.
